<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="498" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1436,351,594]" pageId="11" pageNumber="498">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,459,485]" pageId="11" pageNumber="498">Remarks.</emphasis>
The occurrence of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Froehlich" authorityYear="2007" box="[538,762,459,485]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ofaye">
<emphasis box="[538,762,459,485]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="498">Anacroneuria ofaye</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a new record for the 
<collectingRegion box="[1036,1165,459,486]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="11" pageNumber="498">Goiás state</collectingRegion>
. The penial armature of the studied specimens is similar to that described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Froehlich, C. G." box="[764,957,495,521]" pageId="11" pageNumber="498" pagination="15 - 24" refId="ref8929" refString="Froehlich, C. G. (2007) Three new species of Anacroneuria (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from State of Mato Grosso do Sul, Brazil. Zootaxa, 1461 (1), 15 - 24. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 1461.1.2" type="journal article" year="2007">Froehlich (2007)</bibRefCitation>
, both in shape and size. However, like in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bispo &amp; Froehlich" authorityYear="2004" box="[151,416,531,557]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brandaoi">
<emphasis box="[151,416,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="498">Anacroneuria brandaoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the variations in penial armature found in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Froehlich" authorityYear="2007" box="[902,995,531,557]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ofaye">
<emphasis box="[902,995,531,557]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="498">A. ofaye</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may slightly overlap those observed in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Zwick, 1972:" authorityYear="1155" box="[151,257,567,593]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Anacroneuria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="498" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="debilis">
<emphasis box="[151,257,567,593]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="498">A. debilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The nymph was described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Novaes, M. C. &amp; Bispo, P. C. &amp; Higuti, J." box="[606,838,567,594]" pageId="11" pageNumber="498" pagination="71 - 77" refId="ref9486" refString="Novaes, M. C., Bispo, P. C. &amp; Higuti, J. (2012) A description of the nymph of Anacroneuria ofaye Froehlich (Plecoptera: Perlidae) and an apparatus for rearing Neotropical stonefly species. Zootaxa, 3547 (1), 71 - 77. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3547.1.7" type="journal article" year="2012">
Novaes 
<emphasis box="[697,746,567,593]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="498">et al</emphasis>
. (2012)
</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
